      "content": "interesting. u said it was a failure for western interventionism though... isn't that a bit of a stretch? i mean, the humanitarian aspect of stopping a massacre was a huge win for international law/norms. why focus so much on the chaos that followed rather than the immediate success of preventing a humanitarian disaster?",
