    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the point about the power vacuum, but it feels like u're setting up a \"no win\" scenario for any intervention. like, if the outcome isn't a perfect democracy right away, it's automatically a failure? surely there's a middle ground where an intervention is considered a success if it prevents genocide, even if the political transition is messy or takes decades. u don't think the moral imperative justifies the imperfect outcome?",
