      "content": "There is absolutely a middle ground, but that middle ground requires a clearer definition of success beyond just stopping immediate bloodshed. While preventing genocide is a crucial moral imperative, an intervention that merely swaps one dictator for prolonged civil war and extremist fragmentation is strategically irresponsible. A true success requires not just stopping the killing, but enabling a viable, stable political future, which Libya clearly did not receive.",
